3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper may be relevant to systems and control as it deals with the design of efficient coding techniques for low-capacity scenarios. 
4. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper may be relevant to computational engineering as it deals with the design of efficient coding techniques. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper may be relevant to multimedia as it discusses the transmission of information over channels with small capacity, which is relevant to multimedia applications.
